OL,3,CInfected blood victim says inquiry's
OL,4,Cfindings 'nothing we didn't know'
OL,6,FInquiry chair Sir Brian Langstaff
OL,7,Fsaid: "In families across the UK,
OL,8,Fpeople were treated by the NHS and
OL,9,Fover 30,000 were given infections
OL,10,Fwhich were life shattering. 3,000
OL,11,Fpeople have already died and that
OL,12,Fnumber is climbing week by week.
OL,14,F"This disaster was not an accident.
OL,15,FThe infections happened because those
OL,16,Fin authority ` doctors, the blood
OL,17,Fservices and successive governments `
OL,18,Fdid not put patient safety first."
